# Anchorpipe Project-wide Rules

- Security: enforce CSP, default security headers; validate inputs (Zod) at edges; CSRF/origin checks; HMAC (X-FR-Sig) for ingestion; idempotency keys; rate limiting.
- CI: required checks (lint, typecheck, build, db-health, openapi-validate, DCO, CodeQL, link-check) must pass.
- Docs: update user and program docs when behavior/config changes.
- Labels: suggest and verify taxonomy (`type:*`, `gate:*`, `area:*`, `priority:*`).
- ADRs: material changes to architecture/security/perf budgets require ADR link in PR.


